6e1_d17517e1_d17518e1\"><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"height: 0px;\"><th aria-controls=\"uvn1665702612860__table_d17516e1_d17517e1_d17518e1\" aria-label=\"Property: activate to sort column ascending\" class=\"entry sorting\" colspan=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"uvn1665702612860__table_d17516e1_d17517e1_d17518e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; border-top-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; height: 0px; width: 376.641px;\"><div class=\"dataTables_sizing\" style=\"height: 0px; overflow: hidden;\">Property</div></th><th aria-controls=\"uvn1665702612860__table_d17516e1_d17517e1_d17518e1\" aria-label=\"Technical Property Name: activate to sort column ascending\" class=\"entry sorting\" colspan=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"uvn1665702612860__table_d17516e1_d17517e1_d17518e1__entry__2\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"padding-top: 0px; padding-bottom: 0px; border-top-width: 0px; border-bottom-width: 0px; height: 0px; width: 281.359px;\"><div class=\"dataTables_sizing\" style=\"height: 0px; overflow: hidden;\">Technical Property Name</div></th></tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row odd\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uvn1665702612860__table_d17516e1_d17517e1_d17518e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bou1665702610816.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bou1665702610816.html\" title=\"The Attach to Window Border (Attach) widget property attaches the widget (or area frame) to one or more form window borders or split bars at runtime. This allows the element to be resized or moved when the window is resized or a split bar moved.\">Attach to Window Border (attach)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uvn1665702612860__table_d17516e1_d17517e1_d17518e1__entry__2\">\n<span class=\"keyword\">Attach</span>\n</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row even\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uvn1665702612860__table_d17516e1_d17517e1_d17518e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kml1665702613321.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kml1665702613321.html\" title=\"Size of the margin in pixels, on all sides of the widget, when it is attached to at least one window border. The value can be the number of pixels (for example, 2px) or classic.\">Attach Margin (AttachMargin)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uvn1665702612860__table_d17516e1_d17517e1_d17518e1__entry__2\">\n<span class=\"keyword\">AttachMargin</span>\n</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row odd\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uvn1665702612860__table_d17516e1_d17517e1_d17518e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cys1665702610904.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cys1665702610904.html\" title=\"The BorderType property is used to display a flat or grooved border around an area frame, grid, or the default entity widget.\">BorderType</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uvn1665702612860__table_d17516e1_d17517e1_d17518e1__entry__2\">\n<span class=\"keyword\">BorderType</span>\n</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row even\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uvn1665702612860__table_d17516e1_d17517e1_d17518e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gkz1665702610994.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gkz1665702610994.html\" title=\"The BorderRadius property causes the border of the area frame or entity to have rounded corners. The degree of rounding is determined by the value of the property.\">Border Radius (BorderRadius)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uvn1665702612860__table_d17516e1_d17517e1_d17518e1__entry__2\">\n<span class=\"keyword\">BorderRadius</span>\n</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row odd\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uvn1665702612860__table_d17516e1_d17517e1_d17518e1__entry__1\"></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uvn1665702612860__table_d17516e1_d17517e1_d17518e1__entry__2\">\n                        Color Properties \n                     </td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row even\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uvn1665702612860__table_d17516e1_d17517e1_d17518e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rwc1665702587483.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rwc1665702587483.html\" title=\"Color to use as the background of the object.\">Background Color (BackColor)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uvn1665702612860__table_d17516e1_d17517e1_d17518e1__entry__2\">\n<span class=\"keyword\">BackColor</span>\n</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row odd\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uvn1665702612860__table_d17516e1_d17517e1_d17518e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rbp1665702587714.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rbp1665702587714.html\" title=\"Color to use as the foreground (usually the text color).\">Foreground Color (ForeColor)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uvn1665702612860__table_d17516e1_d17517e1_d17518e1__entry__2\">\n<span class=\"keyword\">ForeColor</span>\n</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row even\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uvn1665702612860__table_d17516e1_d17517e1_d17518e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mux1665702611074.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mux1665702611074.html\" title=\"The BorderColor property displays a border of the specified color around the area frame or entity. It is applicable only if the BorderType property is flat.\">Border Color (BorderColor)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uvn1665702612860__table_d17516e1_d17517e1_d17518e1__entry__2\">\n<span class=\"keyword\">BorderColor</span>\n</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row odd\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uvn1665702612860__table_d17516e1_d17517e1_d17518e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lpd1665702587794.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lpd1665702587794.html\" title=\"Determines whether the background color is styled with a flat or gradient color.\">Gradient Fill Style (BackColorFill)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uvn1665702612860__table_d17516e1_d17517e1_d17518e1__entry__2\">\n<span class=\"keyword\">BackColorFill</span>\n</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row even\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uvn1665702612860__table_d17516e1_d17517e1_d17518e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kto1665702611220.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kto1665702611220.html\" title=\"The BackColorStart widget property determines the color used at the start of a gradient background in an area frame for entity. The default is white.\">Gradient Color Start (BackColorStart)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uvn1665702612860__table_d17516e1_d17517e1_d17518e1__entry__2\">\n<span class=\"keyword\">BackcolorStart</span>\n</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row odd\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uvn1665702612860__table_d17516e1_d17517e1_d17518e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mat1665702611295.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mat1665702611295.html\" title=\"The GradientStart property defines the edge of the area frame or entity from which to start shading the gradient background color. The shading ends at the opposite side.\">Gradient Start ( GradientStart)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uvn1665702612860__table_d17516e1_d17517e1_d17518e1__entry__2\">\n<span class=\"keyword\">GradientStart</span>\n</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row even\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uvn1665702612860__table_d17516e1_d17517e1_d17518e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ecy1665702611370.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ecy1665702611370.html\" title=\"The DropShadowColor property causes the area frame or entity to be displayed with a 4-pixel shadow of the specified color to the right and bottom of the object.\">Drop Shadow Color ( DropShadowColor)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uvn1665702612860__table_d17516e1_d17517e1_d17518e1__entry__2\">\n<span class=\"keyword\">DropShadowColor</span>\n</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row odd\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uvn1665702612860__table_d17516e1_d17517e1_d17518e1__entry__1\"></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uvn1665702612860__table_d17516e1_d17517e1_d17518e1__entry__2\">\n                        Background Image Properties \n                     </td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row even\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uvn1665702612860__table_d17516e1_d17517e1_d17518e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"scc1665702611448.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/scc1665702611448.html\" title=\"Image used as background for the application window, form, or entity. This property can be set in ProcScript.\">Background Image (BackImage)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uvn1665702612860__table_d17516e1_d17517e1_d17518e1__entry__2\">\n<span class=\"keyword\">BackImage</span>\n</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row odd\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uvn1665702612860__table_d17516e1_d17517e1_d17518e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kmv1665702611521.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kmv1665702611521.html\" title=\"This property determines how the data (text or image) is aligned in the widget, entity, area frame, or window.\">Horizontal Alignment (Halign)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uvn1665702612860__table_d17516e1_d17517e1_d17518e1__entry__2\">\n<span class=\"keyword\">HAlign</span>\n</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row even\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uvn1665702612860__table_d17516e1_d17517e1_d17518e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gvp1665702611605.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gvp1665702611605.html\" title=\"This property determines the vertical alignment of data (text or image) in the widget, entity, area frame, or window.\">Vertical Alignment ( Valign)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uvn1665702612860__table_d17516e1_d17517e1_d17518e1__entry__2\">\n<span class=\"keyword\">VAlign</span>\n</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row odd\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uvn1665702612860__table_d17516e1_d17517e1_d17518e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dbd1665702611680.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dbd1665702611680.html\" title=\"This property determines how the image is horizontally scaled; valid only for Image data types. Default value is 100 (percent).\">Horizontal Scaling ( Hscale)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uvn1665702612860__table_d17516e1_d17517e1_d17518e1__entry__2\">\n<span class=\"keyword\">Hscale</span>\n</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row even\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uvn1665702612860__table_d17516e1_d17517e1_d17518e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"sup1665702611757.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sup1665702611757.html\" title=\"This property determines how the image is scaled vertically; valid only for Image data types. Default value is 100 (percent).\">Vertical Scaling ( Vscale)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uvn1665702612860__table_d17516e1_d17517e1_d17518e1__entry__2\">\n<span class=\"keyword\">VScale</span>\n</td>\n</tr><tr class=\"row odd\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uvn1665702612860__table_d17516e1_d17517e1_d17518e1__entry__1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yxe1665702611833.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yxe1665702611833.html\" title=\"Determines whether the aspect ratio of the image is preserved at all times. True (default) or False.\">Preserve Aspect Ratio ( PreserveAspect)</a>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"uvn1665702612860__table_d17516e1_d17517e1_d17518e1__entry__2\">\n<span class=\"keyword\">PreserveAspect</span>\n</td>\n</tr></tbody></table></div><div class=\"dataTables_scrollFoot\" style=\"overflow: hidden; border: 0px; width: 100%;\"><div class=\"dataTables_scrollFootInner\"><table class=\"table dataTable no-footer\" count-columns=\"2\" style=\"margin-left: 0px;\"><tfoot></tfoot></table></div></div></div></div></div>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"uvn1665702612860__table_d17522e1_d17523e1_d17524e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Default value:</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">None</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> File section:</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ila1665702671184.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ila1665702671184.html\" title=\"The [application] section of the initialization file enables you to set application-level defaults for a Windows desktop application.\">[application]</a>  and/or <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"crw1665702612934.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/crw1665702612934.html\" title=\"Use the [ENTITIES] section of the assignment file to direct individual entities to a path, give the target database table a different name than the name of the entity, or specify the physical file name for database tables for record-level databases.\">[ENTITIES]</a>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"uvn1665702612860__note_kwk_hjc_xvb\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> When defined in both locations, the\n                  definition in the [entities] is used.</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"uvn1665702612860__section_mjf_z2c_xvb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d307966e557\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">udefentity</code> widget is used when the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Widget Type</span>\n        property of the entity is set to <code class=\"ph codeph\">U_NONE</code> and the Form runs on Windows.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">If defined, the properties set with DefEntity are applied to all entities in the\n        application. You can override these defaults for specific entities by editing widget\n        properties for the modeled entity or the component entity in the Uniface IDE.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">You can change the runtime values of entity widget properties using the\n          <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$entityproperties</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$CurEntProperties</span> ProcScript\n        functions.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"uvn1665702612860__section_fjx_lbv_cdc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d307966e587\">Example: Setting DefEntity</h2>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"uvn1665702612860__pre_n11_nbv_cdc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[application]\nDefEntity=udefentity(backcolor=#deefff)</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/iic1718342502908.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>udefentity (Default Entity Widget )</a><p>The udefentity widget is the default widget for entities in form components. It is a multi-occurrence list, with a minimum of one occurrence, in which fields can be freely arranged. Uniface provides a default logical widget called DefEntity that is mapped to this widget.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rij1704707370362.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Entity Widgets</a><p>In Form and Dynamic Server Page components, you can manipulate the appearance of an entity or occurrence by setting its widget properties, even if there is no entity widget explicitly available.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/giw1665702613626.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$CurEntProperties</a><p>Set properties for an inner entity within the current occurrence of its parent entity.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tlm1665702687704.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$entityproperties</a><p>Return or set the current representation properties of an entity.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532862\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532862\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "DefEntity Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 21, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Logical widget for styling the default entity widget udefentity in Form components. The properties set are applied to all entities in the application. If DefEntity is not defined, the udefentity widget is transparent and follows Windows conventions. DefEntity = udefentity ( Properties ) Arguments Properties —semi-colon delimited list of property-value pairs Search: Column Property Technical Property Name Filter results... 19 rows found Export to Excel Export to CSV Table 1. Widget Properties of Default Entity Widget ( udefentity ) Property Technical Property Name Filter 19 rows found Filter 19 rows found Property Technical Property Name Attach to Window Border (attach) Attach Attach Margin (AttachMargin) AttachMargin BorderType BorderType Border Radius (BorderRadius) BorderRadius Color Properties Background Color (BackColor) BackColor Foreground Color (ForeColor) ForeColor Border Color (BorderColor) BorderColor Gradient Fill Style (BackColorFill) BackColorFill Gradient Color Start (BackColorStart) BackcolorStart Gradient Start ( GradientStart) GradientStart Drop Shadow Color ( DropShadowColor) DropShadowColor Background Image Properties Background Image (BackImage) BackImage Horizontal Alignment (Halign) HAlign Vertical Alignment ( Valign) VAlign Horizontal Scaling ( Hscale) Hscale Vertical Scaling ( Vscale) VScale Preserve Aspect Ratio ( PreserveAspect) PreserveAspect Default value: None File section: [application] and/or [ENTITIES] Note: When defined in both locations, the definition in the [entities] is used. Description The udefentity widget is used when the Widget Type property of the entity is set to U_NONE and the Form runs on Windows. If defined, the properties set with DefEntity are applied to all entities in the application. You can override these defaults for specific entities by editing widget properties for the modeled entity or the component entity in the Uniface IDE. You can change the runtime values of entity widget properties using the $entityproperties and $CurEntProperties ProcScript functions. Example: Setting DefEntity [application] DefEntity=udefentity(backcolor=#deefff) Copy Related Links udefentity (Default Entity Widget ) The udefentity widget is the default widget for entities in form components. It is a multi-occurrence list, with a minimum of one occurrence, in which fields can be freely arranged. Uniface provides a default logical widget called DefEntity that is mapped to this widget. Entity Widgets In Form and Dynamic Server Page components, you can manipulate the appearance of an entity or occurrence by setting its widget properties, even if there is no entity widget explicitly available. $CurEntProperties Set properties for an inner entity within the current occurrence of its parent entity. $entityproperties Return or set the current representation properties of an entity. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}